Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
update_module_model(25.10)                          update_module_model(25.10)

Name
       update_module_model  - Invokes an independent session in interactive or
       batch mode at top-level design

Syntax
       update_module_model

       [-help]

       [-cpu <number_of_cpus>]

       [-distribute_job]

       [-eco_report]

       [-log_dir <dir_name>]

       [-return_tag <tag_name>]

       [-return_type {lef flexIlm ilm pnr}]

       [-tag <tag_name>]

       { [-cell <cell_name>] [-distribute_run ] [ -interactive  |  -plugin_tcl
       <tcl_commands> | -gen_eco_only ]}

       Invokes  an  independent  session  in interactive or batch mode at top-
       level design. The update_module_model command can  be  called  at  top-
       level design.

       Note:  When  an  independent session is invoked, the license(s) will be
       checked-out from the main Innovus session and checked in to  the  inde-
       pendent  session. Once you exit the independent session, the license(s)
       will return back to main Innovus session.

       The update_module_model command:

              * automatically updates the changes from top to block in an  in-
                dependent session.

              * runs the user-provided plug-in commands in batch mode.

              * automatically  brings  back the updated LEF models of the same
                tag to the top-level once the job is done.

       Note: You should run the create_module_model command to save  different
       types of models at the end of an independent session.

Parameters
       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies which cell the command will update changes.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -cpu <number_of_cpus>
              Specifies  the number of CPUs that will be used for the indepen-
              dent session. By default it uses the same of number of  CPUs  as
              its parent.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -distribute_job
              Enables  distributed processing where more than one block design
              can be run in parallel.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -distribute_run
              Enables you to execute  all  the  specified  update_module_model
              distributed jobs using a Makefile.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -eco_report
              Specifies  the  output  report file that contains the ECO change
              information.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -gen_eco_only
              Generates an eco file that  contains  general  netlist  ECO  and
              placement changes. This mode allows you to explicitly review the
              ECO before applying it to the block DB.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each update_module_model parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man update_module_model

       -interactive
              Invokes independent session in interactive mode.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -log_dir <dir_name>
              Specifies the log file directory name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -plugin_tcl <tcl_commands>
              Specifies the TCL commands to be run in a batch independent ses-
              sion.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -return_tag <tag_name>
              Specifies the tag name that will be used to update the specified
              cell model at the top-level design.

              Default:  The  default return tag is the tag name of the current
              loaded block design.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -return_type {flexIlm ilm lef pnr}
              Specifies the model type to be brought back to top-level design.
              The return type can be lef, flexIlm, ilm, or pnr.

              Default: lef

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -tag <tag_name>
              Allows you to explicitly specify the tag name of  the  cell  pnr
              model  that  will  be loaded. If a tag is not specified, the up-
              date_module_model command loads the pnr model of  the  same  tag
              with the currently loaded design (restore_module_model).

              For  example,  if the currently loaded design has tag init, then
              the update_module_model command will load the pnr model  of  tag
              init for the specified cell. It will display an error if the tag
              is not available.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              *

                The  following  command  opens an independent session in batch
                mode for the full DB of the cell tdsp_core, tag preCts:

                update_module_model -cell  tdsp_core  -return_type  ilm  -plu-
                gin_tcl {

                 route_eco

                 create_module_model

                }

